@startuml

title Transaction-Level Advisory Lock (Short Transaction Mutex)

participant "Local Demo\n(demoMutex.js)" as DEMO
participant "Attempt 1\nSequelize Tx" as TX1
participant "Attempt 2\nSequelize Tx" as TX2
database "PostgreSQL" as PG
participant "Counter Table\n(counters.id=1)" as COUNTER

== Concurrent local attempts ==
DEMO -> DEMO: Promise.allSettled(5 attempts)
DEMO -> TX1: tryTransactionMutexIncrement(2000)
DEMO -> TX2: tryTransactionMutexIncrement(2000)

activate TX1
TX1 -> PG: BEGIN
TX1 -> PG: SELECT pg_try_advisory_xact_lock(TX_MUTEX_LOCK_KEY)
PG --> TX1: true (lock acquired)
TX1 -> COUNTER: SELECT counter WHERE id = 1
COUNTER --> TX1: value = N

activate TX2
TX2 -> PG: BEGIN
TX2 -> PG: SELECT pg_try_advisory_xact_lock(TX_MUTEX_LOCK_KEY)
PG --> TX2: false (already held by Attempt 1)
TX2 -> PG: ROLLBACK
TX2 --> DEMO: { locked: false, message: "Could not acquire..." }
deactivate TX2

TX1 -> TX1: sleep(delayMs)
TX1 -> COUNTER: UPDATE value = N + 1
TX1 -> PG: COMMIT
note right of PG
xact advisory lock is auto-released
on commit/rollback
end note
TX1 --> DEMO: { locked: true, currentValue: N+1 }
deactivate TX1

DEMO -> DEMO: print one success and skipped attempts

@enduml
